Kosachev: At the 73rd session of the UN General Assembly the theme of Russia in a negative way was practically absent
The head of the Federation Council Committee on international Affairs Konstantin Kosachev considers the 73rd session of the UN General Assembly successful for Russia and does not exclude that it can be a turning point in the perception of the Russian Federation as an integral participant in solving global problems.
"The uniqueness of the current 73rd session, in my opinion, is that the rhetoric, to which we have almost become accustomed in recent years in relation to Russia, was now much more muted," - said the Senator in an interview published on Sunday "Rossiyskaya Gazeta".
He explained that in previous years, the Russian Federation was sometimes "designated as one of the three main threats to humanity, along with Ebola, along with climate change or terrorism, Russia was in this series, at least, in the statement of the group of Western countries, which in this regard was expressed quite unanimously".
At the 73rd session, Kosachev stressed, "the theme of Russia in a negative way was practically absent."
"If you carefully analyze the speech of the President of the United States, the President of France, the speech of the Minister of foreign Affairs of Germany, I now do not take Ukraine, Georgia, or the British, in any case, the choir was not exactly" - drew the attention of the politician, noting that Russia "was no longer a kind of wall, which is trained tennis ball strikes."
The head of the relevant Committee of the Federation Council does not exclude that this indicates a certain trend, which, in his opinion, "will highlight the current session [of the UN General Assembly], although this trend may fully manifest itself in a year, two, three."
"I do not exclude that the current session in some sense can be a turning point," Kosachev admitted, explaining that "there are too many examples of how Russia manages to move forward in international Affairs with the connection."
As an example, he cited the situation in Syria, around Iran and North Korea.
"Unfortunately, this is not Ukraine yet, but I have no doubt that the Russian vision of the Ukrainian crisis will also be in demand over time," the parliamentarian added.
This is due to the fact, he believes, that there is "an adequate, sound perception of Russia as not just a possible - an integral participant in the solution of global problems of our time."
"I would not like to make a mistake, but I have a feeling that we are somewhere passing the point where the movement will not be a movement backwards, it will be a movement forward," he added.
Another "interesting and important feeling" in this context, Kosachev called "a request for a Russian vision of how the modern world should develop."
"I attended many meetings of the head of the Russian delegation [at the session of the General Assembly], foreign Minister Sergey Lavrov, I held my own meetings, and I was very pleased to see that if a year or two or five years ago, Russian opinion, Russian vision of what is happening in the world, by and large, no one was interested, now the situation is different," - said the Chairman of the Federation Council Committee.
In his opinion, this is due to the fact that "the so-called new liberal order, which is personified with the West, has no answers to the questions of how to solve the world's problems due to the obvious lack of ideas in the global space, lack of ideas on how to solve the problems of the Middle East, the problems of terrorism, the problem of non-proliferation of nuclear weapons, the problem of migration."
"And here the request for the Russian vision is becoming more and more obvious," Kosachev expressed confidence, stressing that he believes in this sense, "the current session is successful for the work of the Russian delegation, successful for Russia."
