The main Macedonian opposition leader refused to vote in the referendum
In Macedonia, on Sunday, September 30, a referendum on an intergovernmental Treaty with Greece on the renaming of the Republic of Macedonia is held.
Citizens are asked to answer one question: "do You Support EU and NATO membership by adopting an agreement between the Republic of Macedonia and the Republic of Greece?"
Nevertheless, the leader of the leading opposition party "Internal Macedonian revolutionary organization - Democratic party for Macedonian national unity" (VMRO-DPMNE) Christian Mickoski said that he would not vote in the referendum.
