The Finance Ministry predicted the ruble for 17 years ahead
The Ministry of Finance expects a gradual weakening of the ruble to 73.9 rubles per dollar by 2031-2035, follows from the draft long-term budget forecast submitted to the state Duma together with the draft Federal budget.
In 2021-2025, the ruble exchange rate, according to the forecast, will be 66.4 rubles per dollar, in 2026-2030 - 71.1 rubles, and in the next five years - 73.9.
The office notes that these figures are the nominal rate.
The real effective exchange rate (an indicator that takes into account the change in exchange rates of the countries that are the main trading partners of the Russian Federation) will remain stable, officials assure.
As for inflation, until 2020 it will be 3.5%, and then stabilized at about 4%, according to the Ministry of Finance.
